RISE ASCII SCENE 5
#############################################################################################################
#                                      RISE Ascii Scene File                                                #
#                                                                                                           #
#   File:           pt_alchemists_sanctum.RISEscene                                                         #
#   Description:    Participating-media torture test: "The Alchemist's Sanctum"                             #
#                                                                                                           #
#                   An underground chamber where magical artifacts sit amid layered fog and                  #
#                   refracted light.  The scene exercises every medium-transport path:                       #
#                                                                                                           #
#                   MEDIA TOPOLOGY:                                                                         #
#                     - Global haze: thin golden atmospheric fog (forward-scatter g=0.76)                   #
#                       filling the entire chamber.  Makes light shafts visible.                             #
#                     - Crystal orb: glass sphere (IOR 1.52) with dense amber interior fog.                 #
#                       Tests IOR-stack medium tracking and volumetric caustics (light                       #
#                       refracts through glass into the fog, scatters forward, glows).                      #
#                     - Elixir vial: smaller glass sphere with emerald-green interior fog.                  #
#                       Second IOR-stack + per-object medium instance.                                      #
#                     - Summoned mist: pure-volume sphere (casts_shadows FALSE) of blue                     #
#                       ethereal fog hovering above the scene.  Tests disjoint shadow-ray                    #
#                       medium walk (shadow rays from the floor discover the mist volume                    #
#                       along the path and attenuate).                                                      #
#                     - Mist core: denser cyan fog sphere nested inside the summoned mist.                  #
#                       Tests nested overlapping media in the shadow-walk boundary stack.                    #
#                     - Overlapping aureole: a second pure-volume sphere that partially                     #
#                       overlaps the summoned mist.  Tests non-LIFO stack removal when                      #
#                       the shadow walk exits the aureole before the mist.                                  #
#                                                                                                           #
#                   LIGHTING:                                                                               #
#                     - Narrow skylight slot overhead creates a defined shaft of warm light                  #
#                       through the global haze.  Volumetric shadows are cast by the fog                    #
#                       spheres (colored shadow patches on the floor).                                      #
#                     - Small bright omni light behind the glass lens to drive refracted                    #
#                       caustic beams through the fog.                                                      #
#                                                                                                           #
#                   GEOMETRY:                                                                               #
#                     - Glass lens (CSG sphere intersection) focuses light into the fog.                    #
#                     - Polished stone floor shows colored shadow patches from fog volumes.                  #
#                     - Copper pedestal and mirror sphere for complex indirect paths.                        #
#                                                                                                           #
#                   EXPECTED VISUAL RESULT:                                                                  #
#                     - Warm light shaft from skylight visible in global haze                                #
#                     - Crystal orb glows amber from internal forward-scattered light                        #
#                     - Blue mist sphere casts blue-tinted shadow on the floor                               #
#                     - Within the blue shadow, a deeper cyan patch from the nested core                    #
#                     - Green elixir sphere casts green-tinted shadow                                        #
#                     - Aureole overlap region shows combined attenuation with mist                          #
#                     - Caustic beam from lens visible as bright streak in the haze                          #
#                     - Polished floor reflects all fog volumes                                              #
#                                                                                                           #
#   Author:         Aravind Krishnaswamy                                                                    #
#   Birthdate:      April 1, 2026                                                                           #
#                                                                                                           #
#############################################################################################################

> set accelerator B 10 8

##################################################
# Renderer
##################################################

pathtracing_shaderop
{
	name		pt
	branch		false
}

standard_shader
{
	name		global
	shaderop	pt
}

pixelpel_rasterizer
{
	max_recursion		14
	min_importance		0.0005
	samples				512
	lum_samples			1
	ior_stack			TRUE
}

file_rasterizeroutput
{
	pattern				rendered/pt_alchemists_sanctum
	type				HDR
	bpp					16
	color_space			ROMMRGB_Linear
}

file_rasterizeroutput
{
	pattern				rendered/pt_alchemists_sanctum
	type				PNG
	bpp					8
	color_space			sRGB
}

##################################################
# Camera
#
# Dramatic low angle from the front-right corner,
# looking across the chamber toward the artifacts.
# The skylight shaft and fog volumes are all visible.
##################################################

pinhole_camera
{
	location			4.5 2.8 9.0
	lookat				-0.5 1.8 2.0
	up					0 1 0
	width				768
	height				512
	fov					58.0
}

##################################################
# Participating Media
#
# Six distinct media exercising the full transport:
#   1. Global haze     (scene-wide, forward-scatter)
#   2. Orb interior    (per-object, glass-enclosed)
#   3. Elixir interior (per-object, glass-enclosed)
#   4. Summoned mist   (per-object, pure volume)
#   5. Mist core       (per-object, nested in #4)
#   6. Aureole         (per-object, overlapping #4)
##################################################

# 1. Global haze: very thin golden fog.
#    sigma_t ~ 0.003 per unit.  Room is ~12 units across
#    so optical depth ~ 0.036 — subtle but visible shafts.
#    Forward-scattering (g=0.76) concentrates scattered light
#    near the beam direction, making shafts well-defined.
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		global_haze
	absorption	0.0003 0.0002 0.0006
	scattering	0.0025 0.0022 0.0015
	phase		hg 0.76
}

> set global_medium global_haze

# 2. Crystal orb interior: dense amber smoke.
#    Strong blue absorption gives a warm amber glow.
#    Forward-scatter g=0.65 creates directional glow
#    from the light entering through the glass shell.
#    Sphere radius 1.3, optical depth ~ 2.6*0.9 ~ 2.3
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		orb_fog
	absorption	0.08 0.25 0.90
	scattering	0.25 0.22 0.12
	phase		hg 0.65
}

# 3. Elixir vial: emerald-green fog.
#    Absorbs red and blue, transmits green.
#    Sphere radius 0.55, optical depth ~ 1.1*0.8 ~ 0.9
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		elixir_fog
	absorption	0.60 0.06 0.55
	scattering	0.15 0.20 0.15
	phase		hg 0.4
}

# 4. Summoned mist: ethereal blue-violet haze.
#    Absorbs red/green, transmits blue.  Moderate density.
#    Sphere radius 1.1, optical depth ~ 2.2*0.35 ~ 0.77
#    casts_shadows FALSE on the object — only the medium
#    walk discovers this volume along shadow rays.
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		mist_fog
	absorption	0.18 0.12 0.01
	scattering	0.12 0.10 0.15
	phase		hg 0.3
}

# 5. Mist core: dense luminous cyan, nested inside #4.
#    Stronger scattering, very low red absorption.
#    Sphere radius 0.35, optical depth ~ 0.7*1.2 ~ 0.84
#    The shadow walk pushes mist_fog, then pushes core_fog
#    (core becomes active), pops core, pops mist.
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		core_fog
	absorption	0.40 0.10 0.02
	scattering	0.50 0.45 0.60
	phase		hg 0.0
}

# 6. Aureole: warm golden wisp overlapping the mist.
#    Partially overlaps summoned mist to test non-LIFO
#    stack removal in the shadow walk.
#    Sphere radius 0.7, optical depth ~ 1.4*0.3 ~ 0.42
homogeneous_medium
{
	name		aureole_fog
	absorption	0.04 0.08 0.25
	scattering	0.10 0.10 0.06
	phase		hg 0.5
}

